headlines.description: — When Luka Doncic's pass to Reggie Bullock with a second left in regulation led to a missed shot, the Dallas Mavericks weren't discouraged.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic has 41 in triple-double, Mavs beat Nets 129-125 in OT

events.name: LA Clippers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — The Thunder have done it again.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 24 as Thunder beat Clippers again

events.name: Miami Heat at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Smooth as ever starting his 14th NBA season, Stephen Curry shook Tyler Herro and made it look oh so easy.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 33 as Warriors hold off Heat 123-110

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane made six 3-pointers and scored 31 points as the Memphis Grizzlies defeated the winless Sacramento Kings 125-110 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane scores 31, Morant 22 as Grizzlies beat Kings 125-110
